This notebook provides some basic exploratory analysis of games on boardgamegeek (BGG) in support of my work [predicting ratings for upcoming games] and [predicting games for individual users].

For this write up, I examine games published through 2022 that have achieved at least 25 user ratings by the time of writing.[^ I have additionally excluded some games that were cancelled or never released, or have data quality issues with their profiles on BGG.]

Who are the top publishers of games on BGG and how do they relate to community ratings?

1.2 Publisher Partial Effects

Which publishers have the largest effect on a games average? Users rated?

We could simply look at the games published by each publisher and then take their average rating/average number of user ratings. However, this doesnt account for the fact that some publishers design more complex games than others, or that recently published games tend to have higher averages.
